import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='population', y='engineers')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between population and number of engineers in each state?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='hurricanes', data=data)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest number of hurricanes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    max_hurricanes_state = data.loc[data['hurricanes'].idxmax()]['state']
    max_hurricanes = data['hurricanes'].max()
    chart.axhline(max_hurricanes, ls='--', color='red', label=f'Max: {max_hurricanes_state} ({max_hurricanes:.2f})')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
